<h2>The weather in April 2021</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
In the major part of Europe temperatures were exceptionally below the 30-year average (Figure 6). On the contrary, in northeast and southwest Europe the temperatures were far above the climatological mean. April 2021 was a very cold and frosty month. Already after the first two-thirds of the month, many places e.g. in the United Kingdom and in Switzerland had seen at least twice as many frosty nights than on average, and new records of the number of frost days were recorded in places e.g. in France and Austria.
